Octave Collapsed Gibbs Sampler

Source code from this site:

http://www.ics.uci.edu/~asuncion/software/fast.htm

"Distributed collapsed Gibbs sampling for LDA"

References
  D. Newman, A. Asuncion, P. Smyth, M. Welling.
    "Distributed Algorithms for Topic Models."
      JMLR 2009.

  D. Newman, A. Asuncion, P. Smyth, M. Welling.
    "Distributed Inference for Latent Dirichlet Allocation."
      NIPS 2007.

To run the code type './RUNDEMO.sh'

The file gibbs.m is an octave implementation of gibbsMex.c

To compile and test gibbsMex.c, type
  mkoctfile --mex gibbsMex.c
  swap commented lines 72/73 in 'distributedLDAsampler.m' 
   
